\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 Inevitables tend to stick out in a crowd while they\rquote 
re in observation mode, but they seem oblivious to the attention. Their forms vary,
 but all inevitables are gold-and-silver clockwork creatures, with gears and pistons where muscles would be on flesh-and-blood creatures. Their eyes glow with a golden radiance.
\par Note that unlike most constructs, inevitables have an Intelligence score and can think, learn, and remember.
\par Inevitables speak Abyssal, Celestial, Infernal, and the native language of their first target.
\par }{COMBAT
\par }{\fs20 Unless their very existence is threatened, inevitables focus completely on the transgressor they\rquote ve been assigned to, ignoring other combatants completely. An inevitable might attack anyone who hinders its progress, but it won\rquote 
t tarry beyond the point where it can reengage its quarry. Inevitables take self-defense very seriously; anyone who attacks an inevitable with what the creature perceives as deadly force is met with deadly force in return.
\par An inevitable\rquote s natural weapons, as well as any weapons it wields, are treated as lawful-aligned for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction.
\par }{\b\fs20 Fast Healing (Ex): }{\fs20 An inevitable heals a certain amount of damage each round (specified in each variety\rquote s description) as long as it has at least 1 hit point. However, damage dealt by chaotic weapons heals at the normal rate.

